1
00:00:45,719 --> 00:00:49,546
<i>Look high in the sky
on this Never Land night.</i>

2
00:00:49,799 --> 00:00:54,319
<i>For a glowing, green star
the fourth from the right.</i>

3
00:00:54,320 --> 00:00:58,319
<i>As it falls from the heavens
and streaks through the air.</i>

4
00:00:58,320 --> 00:01:02,719
<i>You will know it is a comet
a sight strange and rare.</i>

5
00:01:02,719 --> 00:01:06,102
<i>A harmless display?
A treat for the eye? </i>

6
00:01:06,239 --> 00:01:07,478
<i>Perhaps.</i>

7
00:01:07,480 --> 00:01:11,387
<i>But be careful
for appearances lie.</i>

8
00:01:11,640 --> 00:01:15,558
<i>This comet, you see
has been here before.</i>

9
00:01:15,560 --> 00:01:20,228
<i>The ancients described it
in old fairy lore.</i>

10
00:01:21,039 --> 00:01:25,039
<i>Beware the green tail
as it trails along side.</i>

11
00:01:25,039 --> 00:01:29,140
<i>And spills into corners
where shadows abide.</i>

12
00:01:29,480 --> 00:01:32,799
<i>Take heeds, and you will know
that before the dawn breaks.</i>

13
00:01:32,799 --> 00:01:36,820
<i>"Deep down in the darkness
something awakes"</i>

14
00:01:42,879 --> 00:01:49,625
TINKER BEll AND THE LEGEND OF
NEVER BEAST
Translation and Review
By Angel

15
00:02:04,200 --> 00:02:06,548
<i>♪ I am going to fall.</i>

16
00:02:07,280 --> 00:02:12,438
<i>♪ Head first and fast like
an avalanche.</i>

17
00:02:12,439 --> 00:02:14,867
<i>♪ Maybe I will land.</i>

18
00:02:15,319 --> 00:02:16,679
<i>♪ Maybe I will crash.</i>

19
00:02:16,680 --> 00:02:20,540
<i>♪ I will take that chance.</i>

20
00:02:20,759 --> 00:02:25,478
<i>♪ Because there is nothing but air
in between me and everything.</i>

21
00:02:25,479 --> 00:02:29,478
<i>♪ Nothing to keep me
from flying aimlessly.</i>

22
00:02:29,479 --> 00:02:33,359
<i>♪ Shamelessly laughing
at destiny.</i>

23
00:02:33,360 --> 00:02:37,438
<i>♪ And no one knows
how high I go.</i>

24
00:02:37,439 --> 00:02:41,300
<i>♪ Or what makes
the atmosphere glow.</i>

25
00:02:41,680 --> 00:02:45,679
<i>♪ I could follow
the narrow road.</i>

26
00:02:45,680 --> 00:02:49,079
<i>♪ But maybe I will let
it all go.</i>

27
00:02:49,079 --> 00:02:53,430
<i>♪ And just float.</i>

28
00:02:57,520 --> 00:03:00,061
<i>♪ I will float.</i>

29
00:03:01,840 --> 00:03:04,062
<i>♪ Float.</i>

30
00:03:11,759 --> 00:03:13,983
Tinker, it is perfect!

31
00:03:14,360 --> 00:03:15,959
Just like you ordered, Fawn.

32
00:03:15,960 --> 00:03:19,359
One extra-large wagon.
What for is it?

33
00:03:19,360 --> 00:03:21,199
I mean, why is all the mystery?

34
00:03:21,199 --> 00:03:23,919
I just love how your
mind is always working.

35
00:03:23,920 --> 00:03:25,878
I can take it from here.

36
00:03:25,879 --> 00:03:28,998
Baby ducklings!
Or baby bunnies?

37
00:03:29,000 --> 00:03:31,223
It is a movable nursery,
Right?

38
00:03:31,800 --> 00:03:32,878
Bull is eye!

39
00:03:32,879 --> 00:03:34,878
I cannot get a thing past you,
Tinker.

40
00:03:34,879 --> 00:03:37,639
Well, anyway, catch you later.

41
00:03:37,639 --> 00:03:39,478
You are up to something.

42
00:03:39,479 --> 00:03:41,639
Who, me? Never.

43
00:03:41,639 --> 00:03:43,862
Yep, you definitely are.

44
00:03:43,879 --> 00:03:45,158
I know that Look.

45
00:03:45,159 --> 00:03:48,703
I invented that look.
What for is the wagon?

46
00:03:49,120 --> 00:03:53,478
Okay, okay.
Just try not to scream.

47
00:03:53,479 --> 00:03:54,781
Deal?

48
00:04:00,479 --> 00:04:03,306
No deal. No deal. No deal!

49
00:04:04,000 --> 00:04:05,919
It is okay, Hannah.

50
00:04:05,919 --> 00:04:07,346
Tinker is with me.

51
00:04:07,479 --> 00:04:08,718
You have a...

52
00:04:08,719 --> 00:04:09,838
Deep breathe in.

53
00:04:09,840 --> 00:04:10,878
...Hawk!

54
00:04:10,879 --> 00:04:12,318
Yep.

55
00:04:12,319 --> 00:04:14,679
Fawn, hawks eats fairies!

56
00:04:14,680 --> 00:04:16,399
Adult hawks, yes.

57
00:04:16,399 --> 00:04:18,559
Hannah is still technically
a baby.

58
00:04:18,560 --> 00:04:22,639
That whole "must-eat-fairy" urges
has not quite kicked in yet.

59
00:04:22,639 --> 00:04:24,478
She does not look so
babyish to me.

60
00:04:24,480 --> 00:04:26,199
Well, she was when
I brought her here.

61
00:04:26,199 --> 00:04:29,559
She had a bad wing,
but I fixed her up and now...

62
00:04:32,439 --> 00:04:33,838
Wing is all better.

63
00:04:33,840 --> 00:04:36,879
You cannot have a hawk
in Pixie Hollow.

64
00:04:36,879 --> 00:04:38,519
What if the Scouts find out?

65
00:04:38,519 --> 00:04:40,798
That is where the blueberry
wagon comes in!

66
00:04:40,800 --> 00:04:42,879
We just have to get Hannah
out to where she belongs

67
00:04:42,879 --> 00:04:45,358
without causing, you know...

68
00:04:45,360 --> 00:04:46,821
...Widespread panic.

69
00:04:55,040 --> 00:04:56,199
Good job!

70
00:04:56,199 --> 00:04:57,278
Here you go.

71
00:04:57,279 --> 00:04:58,581
Good.

72
00:05:00,560 --> 00:05:02,278
You are doing great,
Hannah.

73
00:05:02,279 --> 00:05:03,999
Hang tight until we are in
the clear.

74
00:05:04,000 --> 00:05:06,119
Are you sure about this,
Fawn?

75
00:05:06,120 --> 00:05:09,158
Remember, we are just taking
berries to the forest.

76
00:05:09,160 --> 00:05:10,278
Nothing to it.

77
00:05:10,279 --> 00:05:14,106
But do not berries usually
come from the forest?

78
00:05:16,240 --> 00:05:17,798
Everything will be fine.

79
00:05:17,800 --> 00:05:19,589
Just fly casual.

80
00:05:20,000 --> 00:05:23,559
Exactly how often
do you do this kind of thing?

81
00:05:23,560 --> 00:05:25,759
Come on.

82
00:05:33,680 --> 00:05:34,838
Fawn?

83
00:05:34,840 --> 00:05:37,221
Just keep smiling.

84
00:05:39,480 --> 00:05:41,718
See, Tinker? I told you
this would work.

85
00:05:41,720 --> 00:05:44,918
All you need is a little faith,
trust, and...

86
00:05:44,920 --> 00:05:45,959
Pixie dust?

87
00:05:45,959 --> 00:05:47,079
There you are!

88
00:05:47,079 --> 00:05:48,959
We have been looking for you
all morning!

89
00:05:48,959 --> 00:05:50,759
Did you guys see
that comet last night?

90
00:05:50,759 --> 00:05:54,798
No, but did you see that big
green ball of light that flew by?

91
00:05:54,800 --> 00:05:55,999
What is with the berries?

92
00:05:56,000 --> 00:05:58,079
Just bringing them to the forest.

93
00:05:58,079 --> 00:05:59,745
For the animals.

94
00:05:59,920 --> 00:06:02,620
Do not berries come
from the forest?

95
00:06:03,120 --> 00:06:04,879
Not this particular
variety.

96
00:06:04,879 --> 00:06:10,026
Which is?
Extra berry full delicious tastic!

97
00:06:10,040 --> 00:06:11,639
Can we help?

98
00:06:11,639 --> 00:06:13,278
No, no, no!
We are fine.

99
00:06:13,279 --> 00:06:14,439
Why would we need help?

100
00:06:14,439 --> 00:06:16,119
For goodness'sake.

101
00:06:16,120 --> 00:06:17,918
There is an easier way
to do this.

102
00:06:17,920 --> 00:06:19,678
Wait! No, no!
You do not know what you are doing!

103
00:06:19,680 --> 00:06:21,278
It is called "helping."

104
00:06:21,279 --> 00:06:24,822
A simple "thank you"
would suffice.

105
00:06:25,079 --> 00:06:27,701
What are you all
at staring that?

106
00:06:41,319 --> 00:06:42,620
Hawk!

107
00:06:50,079 --> 00:06:53,079
That comet is an astronomical
puzzle, to be sure,

108
00:06:53,079 --> 00:06:54,519
but careful observation,

109
00:06:54,519 --> 00:06:56,389
and application...

110
00:07:06,360 --> 00:07:07,661
Hannah!

111
00:07:08,040 --> 00:07:10,387
Hannah, stop!
Come back!

112
00:07:10,680 --> 00:07:12,220
Everyone, get inside!

113
00:07:16,600 --> 00:07:17,980
Iridessa!

114
00:07:22,519 --> 00:07:24,389
No!

115
00:07:28,680 --> 00:07:30,310
Nyx?

116
00:08:09,959 --> 00:08:12,262
Hannah?
Hannah!

117
00:08:13,439 --> 00:08:15,548
Go! Get inside!
Hurry!

118
00:08:15,720 --> 00:08:17,021
Go!

119
00:08:18,319 --> 00:08:19,667
Come on!

120
00:08:59,960 --> 00:09:02,839
Wait! Everybody
calm down!

121
00:09:02,840 --> 00:09:06,719
I promise, she does not even
like the taste of Scout Fairy.

122
00:09:06,720 --> 00:09:09,466
Babies are such picky eaters.

123
00:09:10,960 --> 00:09:13,558
It is okay, Hannah.
Everything is going to be all right.

124
00:09:13,559 --> 00:09:15,429
Get away from the hawk, Fawn.

125
00:09:15,480 --> 00:09:16,958
Let us handle this.

126
00:09:16,960 --> 00:09:18,599
There is nothing to handle, Nyx.

127
00:09:18,600 --> 00:09:20,599
I said stand down, Fawn.

128
00:09:20,600 --> 00:09:22,583
Is everyone all right?

129
00:09:23,519 --> 00:09:26,744
Yes, Queen Clarion, this time.

130
00:09:28,919 --> 00:09:30,519
But how am I suppose
to keep us safe.

131
00:09:30,519 --> 00:09:34,239
If Fawn keeps bringing dangerous
animals into Pixie Hollow?

132
00:09:34,240 --> 00:09:36,860
Last time it was rats,
and a snake!

133
00:09:36,879 --> 00:09:38,959
Actually, last time,
it was a vampire bat.

134
00:09:38,960 --> 00:09:41,759
Fawn  just got a big heart,
that is all.

135
00:09:41,759 --> 00:09:43,519
Hannah needed her help.

136
00:09:43,519 --> 00:09:47,479
Does this look like the face
of a dangerous predator to you?

137
00:09:49,120 --> 00:09:51,078
Come on, back me up, guys!

138
00:09:53,519 --> 00:09:55,318
- Fawn...
- I know, I know.

139
00:09:55,320 --> 00:09:56,438
Nyx is right.

140
00:09:56,440 --> 00:09:59,999
I have done this once or twice,
or several times before.

141
00:10:00,000 --> 00:10:01,198
Yes.

142
00:10:01,200 --> 00:10:05,359
However, perhaps my latest
endeavor was crossing the line.

143
00:10:05,360 --> 00:10:07,038
- Indeed.
- I hear what you are saying.

144
00:10:07,039 --> 00:10:10,900
Maybe harboring a baby hawk
was the best idea.

145
00:10:11,000 --> 00:10:12,918
Fawn, I know you.

146
00:10:12,919 --> 00:10:15,158
You have always let your
heart guides you.

147
00:10:15,159 --> 00:10:17,119
Which is admirable, but...

148
00:10:17,120 --> 00:10:19,821
But I also need to listen
with my head.

149
00:10:22,919 --> 00:10:26,029
Next time, I promise,
I will.

150
00:10:30,720 --> 00:10:33,558
Well, Hannah-Banana,
I had said come back and visit,

151
00:10:33,559 --> 00:10:37,479
but it is probably best to keep this
a long distance thing.

152
00:10:37,480 --> 00:10:40,669
Now, let us try that wing.

153
00:10:57,960 --> 00:10:59,999
Good morning, students!

154
00:11:00,000 --> 00:11:03,038
Beautiful day for a fresh start,
do not you think?

155
00:11:03,039 --> 00:11:06,239
All right, then, let us see
that hopping.

156
00:11:06,240 --> 00:11:08,599
Nice work, Nico.

157
00:11:08,600 --> 00:11:10,389
Perfection, Paige!

158
00:11:11,440 --> 00:11:15,239
Calista, remember it is hopping,
not walking.

159
00:11:17,159 --> 00:11:18,719
What, have not you heard?

160
00:11:18,720 --> 00:11:20,519
I am strictly by the book now.

161
00:11:20,519 --> 00:11:24,187
Yep, we are talking model citizen
all the way.

162
00:11:25,000 --> 00:11:27,558
Looking for the definition
of responsibility?

163
00:11:27,559 --> 00:11:30,703
Look no further than
this girl!

164
00:11:37,080 --> 00:11:40,065
Well, that was interesting.

165
00:11:44,799 --> 00:11:46,318
Now, that is hopping.

166
00:11:54,919 --> 00:11:56,551
Hello?

167
00:12:57,960 --> 00:13:00,399
Come on, Fawn, listen
to your head.

168
00:13:00,399 --> 00:13:03,669
Heart gets you in trouble,
head is your friend.

169
00:13:04,120 --> 00:13:07,399
And yet, head is making me
talk to myself,

170
00:13:07,399 --> 00:13:08,519
out loud,

171
00:13:08,519 --> 00:13:10,198
in the forest.

172
00:13:10,200 --> 00:13:12,662
No, no, no.
Model citizen.

173
00:13:13,879 --> 00:13:15,544
Starting first thing
tomorrow.

174
00:13:52,200 --> 00:13:54,229
What are you?

175
00:14:56,639 --> 00:14:59,318
Okay, think.
Territorial, possibly carnivorous.

176
00:14:59,320 --> 00:15:01,318
Unspeakably big!

177
00:15:01,320 --> 00:15:02,639
What to do?
What to do?

178
00:15:02,639 --> 00:15:04,918
Play dead!

179
00:15:04,919 --> 00:15:06,719
No, no. Freeze.

180
00:15:06,720 --> 00:15:09,879
No, the opposite!
Make myself look big!

181
00:15:22,320 --> 00:15:24,144
What was that?

182
00:15:58,840 --> 00:16:00,078
Did you hear it?

183
00:16:00,080 --> 00:16:01,239
Hear what?

184
00:16:01,240 --> 00:16:02,479
The roar!

185
00:16:02,480 --> 00:16:05,350
Did you hear the roar?

186
00:16:06,039 --> 00:16:08,547
Sorry, did you say something?

187
00:16:10,039 --> 00:16:11,519
You bet I heard it.

188
00:16:11,519 --> 00:16:12,719
Little faster.

189
00:16:12,720 --> 00:16:15,558
Visualize the acorn right
in front of you.

190
00:16:15,559 --> 00:16:17,558
Excellent.
What was it?

191
00:16:17,559 --> 00:16:18,798
No idea.

192
00:16:18,799 --> 00:16:21,625
But let me know as soon as
you find out.

193
00:16:21,720 --> 00:16:23,703
Gently, now. To the left.

194
00:16:23,919 --> 00:16:25,380
No, the other left!

195
00:16:28,240 --> 00:16:29,318
That roars...

196
00:16:29,320 --> 00:16:31,239
- This morning?
- What was it?

197
00:16:31,240 --> 00:16:33,879
I do not know.
I do not specialize in roars.

198
00:16:33,879 --> 00:16:35,838
Now, grunts and growls,
on the other hand...

199
00:16:35,840 --> 00:16:36,999
Who would know?

200
00:16:37,000 --> 00:16:38,759
Well, if it came
from anything big...

201
00:16:38,759 --> 00:16:40,719
- Loud...
- Scary...

202
00:16:40,720 --> 00:16:42,838
And dangerous, try...

203
00:16:42,840 --> 00:16:44,471
Fawn.

204
00:18:00,720 --> 00:18:02,199
Come on, big guy.

205
00:18:02,200 --> 00:18:03,786
Over here.

206
00:18:44,359 --> 00:18:45,999
Wait! I was only
trying to help!

207
00:19:05,440 --> 00:19:08,868
So, I guess I will just be
on my way, then.

208
00:19:15,039 --> 00:19:18,038
Those thick forelimbs
are ideal for digging.

209
00:19:18,039 --> 00:19:19,199
Nope. No, no, no.

210
00:19:19,200 --> 00:19:22,423
You all fixed up,
so off I go!

211
00:19:23,119 --> 00:19:27,199
And that massive jaw is perfect
for supporting those heavy rocks.

212
00:19:28,279 --> 00:19:30,078
Okay. Sorry,
sorry.

213
00:19:30,079 --> 00:19:31,744
Just leaving.

214
00:19:32,799 --> 00:19:35,558
But, you know, it is as if
you are a cross between

215
00:19:35,559 --> 00:19:39,307
<i>Didelphis marsupials
and Bison occidentales...</i>

216
00:19:42,000 --> 00:19:43,519
That spits.

217
00:19:43,519 --> 00:19:45,345
Well, I do not know what
that about is.

218
00:19:46,440 --> 00:19:49,310
And I do not know what
that about is.

219
00:19:52,480 --> 00:19:56,479
I really do not know what about is.
What are you building?

220
00:19:56,480 --> 00:19:59,878
You know, it is my job.
As an Animal Fairy.

221
00:19:59,880 --> 00:20:02,118
To understand and study animals.

222
00:20:02,119 --> 00:20:05,105
And the Queen did say.
I should listen to my head.

223
00:20:07,640 --> 00:20:09,798
You have convinced me.

224
00:20:09,799 --> 00:20:12,785
I will do it for the Queen.

225
00:20:14,200 --> 00:20:15,638
Now stay here.
Okay?

226
00:20:15,640 --> 00:20:17,878
I will be right back.
I just need to get my stuff.

227
00:20:17,880 --> 00:20:19,227
Do not go anywhere.

228
00:20:19,319 --> 00:20:20,959
Just stay.

229
00:20:20,960 --> 00:20:22,785
Stay.

230
00:20:24,440 --> 00:20:25,901
Stay.

231
00:20:34,359 --> 00:20:36,423
Fawn.

232
00:20:37,000 --> 00:20:38,461
Nyx.

233
00:20:38,839 --> 00:20:41,679
I have been looking everywhere
for you. So, where have you been?

234
00:20:41,680 --> 00:20:42,999
Off hiding a hippo?

235
00:20:43,000 --> 00:20:45,318
Yep, he is bunking with
the bobcat.

236
00:20:45,319 --> 00:20:48,099
Did you hear that roar
this morning?

237
00:20:49,160 --> 00:20:50,999
Can you describe the roar
in question?

238
00:20:51,000 --> 00:20:52,519
What kind of roar was it?

239
00:20:52,519 --> 00:20:55,278
The loud, hair rising,
monstrous kind.

240
00:20:55,279 --> 00:20:56,798
Animals make all kinds
of roars.

241
00:20:56,799 --> 00:21:01,583
I mean, you have your growls, howls,
whoops, hollers, shrieks, rumbles.

242
00:21:01,640 --> 00:21:03,278
So. Was it like this?

243
00:21:04,680 --> 00:21:06,358
No. A roar.

244
00:21:06,359 --> 00:21:07,878
As like...

245
00:21:09,079 --> 00:21:10,719
No.

246
00:21:10,720 --> 00:21:12,020
No!

247
00:21:12,039 --> 00:21:13,340
No!

248
00:21:15,599 --> 00:21:18,221
Fawn!

249
00:21:18,359 --> 00:21:20,798
Yeah. If you hear that one. Run.

250
00:21:20,799 --> 00:21:22,101
Would you hand me that?

251
00:21:24,359 --> 00:21:28,159
Look, this thing
might be a threat to Pixie Hollow.

252
00:21:28,160 --> 00:21:32,318
If you find out what made that roar,
I need to know.

253
00:21:32,319 --> 00:21:33,905
Are we clear?

254
00:21:34,359 --> 00:21:36,309
What will you do if
you find it.

255
00:21:37,880 --> 00:21:39,704
My Job.

256
00:21:41,039 --> 00:21:42,759
And I will do mine.

257
00:21:51,559 --> 00:21:53,719
<i>♪ Strange sight.</i>

258
00:21:53,720 --> 00:21:55,838
<i>♪ You stand in the light.</i>

