515
00:38:18,599 --> 00:38:20,039
Giant thing would not budge.

516
00:38:20,039 --> 00:38:22,798
I think he did not want
to leave you.

517
00:38:29,920 --> 00:38:32,159
I missed you too, Gruff.

518
00:38:32,159 --> 00:38:34,918
Sorry to break whatever
this is up.

519
00:38:34,920 --> 00:38:37,278
But what happened
to doing the right thing?

520
00:38:37,280 --> 00:38:38,798
Nyx got there first.

521
00:38:38,800 --> 00:38:40,226
And?

522
00:38:42,599 --> 00:38:43,900
And...

523
00:38:45,320 --> 00:38:47,398
Nyx found this
harebrained legend.

524
00:38:47,400 --> 00:38:49,239
About a creature called
the "Never Beast".

525
00:38:49,239 --> 00:38:53,398
Who builds rock towers and shoots
lightning to destroy Pixie Hollow.

526
00:38:53,400 --> 00:38:57,021
So now she thinks
he is some kind of monster.

527
00:39:00,159 --> 00:39:02,860
I know. Crazy. Right?

528
00:39:06,159 --> 00:39:08,119
Well, early day tomorrow.

529
00:39:08,119 --> 00:39:09,398
Am I tired?

530
00:39:09,400 --> 00:39:10,599
Really? I am wide-awake.

531
00:39:10,599 --> 00:39:12,119
Good-bye, now.

532
00:39:12,119 --> 00:39:13,679
Come on, guys.

533
00:39:13,679 --> 00:39:16,550
You do not really think
any of that stuff is true.

534
00:39:18,559 --> 00:39:22,068
It is just, I know he is not
what they say he is.

535
00:39:24,280 --> 00:39:27,789
Even if you are right,
it is not safe for him here.

536
00:39:58,039 --> 00:40:00,599
Hey, big guy. Done for the day?

537
00:40:00,599 --> 00:40:02,759
Rest up.

538
00:40:02,760 --> 00:40:04,438
Because first thing tomorrow.

539
00:40:04,440 --> 00:40:07,027
We are going to find
some place great for you.

540
00:40:07,159 --> 00:40:09,621
Just until things settle down.

541
00:40:10,599 --> 00:40:13,039
Gruff, you see those stars
over there?

542
00:40:13,039 --> 00:40:16,264
If you connect them,
they make a monkey.

543
00:40:16,360 --> 00:40:18,423
See his tail?

544
00:40:18,440 --> 00:40:22,266
But if you turn it upside down,
it is a swan.

545
00:40:22,360 --> 00:40:23,786
See?

546
00:40:24,440 --> 00:40:25,838
That one is a squirrel.

547
00:40:25,840 --> 00:40:27,559
And over there, with the spikes?

548
00:40:27,559 --> 00:40:29,987
Hedgehog! See it?

549
00:40:32,920 --> 00:40:34,798
I knew you would get it.

550
00:40:34,800 --> 00:40:37,751
You just have to know
how to look.

551
00:40:39,920 --> 00:40:43,190
Imagine. You, a monster.

552
00:40:43,280 --> 00:40:45,679
Of all the ridiculous ideas.

553
00:40:47,079 --> 00:40:49,541
I know they are wrong
about you.

554
00:40:53,199 --> 00:40:55,501
They do not see what I see.

555
00:41:23,679 --> 00:41:25,027
Gruff?

556
00:41:26,920 --> 00:41:28,460
Gruff?

557
00:41:41,880 --> 00:41:43,909
It is starting.

558
00:41:48,920 --> 00:41:50,079
What is that?

559
00:41:50,079 --> 00:41:51,159
It is so green.

560
00:41:51,159 --> 00:41:53,349
I have never seen anything
like that.

561
00:42:01,360 --> 00:42:02,719
Gruff?

562
00:42:02,719 --> 00:42:04,798
Gruff? Come on, Gruff.

563
00:42:04,800 --> 00:42:07,438
It is "chase" the fairy,
not "run away" from her.

564
00:42:07,440 --> 00:42:08,740
Fawn!

565
00:42:09,119 --> 00:42:12,119
The Scouts, they were gear up
and moving fast.

566
00:42:12,119 --> 00:42:14,159
Please tell me
you took him away already.

567
00:42:14,159 --> 00:42:15,278
About that.

568
00:42:15,280 --> 00:42:18,478
I sort of, temporarily,
misplaced him.

569
00:42:18,480 --> 00:42:19,958
You lost him.

570
00:42:19,960 --> 00:42:21,079
I got this.

571
00:42:21,079 --> 00:42:23,701
I just have to find him
before the Scouts do.

572
00:42:23,840 --> 00:42:26,119
Wait! He is going to build
two more towers.

573
00:42:26,119 --> 00:42:28,119
One in Autumn,
one in Winter.

574
00:42:28,119 --> 00:42:30,918
I thought you said
the legend was not real.

575
00:42:30,920 --> 00:42:34,438
Technically,
I said he is not what they think.

576
00:42:34,440 --> 00:42:37,838
But everything Nyx warned us about,
it is happening.

577
00:42:37,840 --> 00:42:39,798
The clouds are green!

578
00:42:39,800 --> 00:42:42,318
Look, it does not matter
what Nyx is legend says.

579
00:42:42,320 --> 00:42:45,543
All I know is, Gruff would
never hurt us.

580
00:42:45,880 --> 00:42:48,547
Please, Tinker. Trust me.

581
00:42:51,079 --> 00:42:52,460
I will take Winter.

582
00:42:53,920 --> 00:42:55,266
Hei? Tinker!

583
00:42:56,320 --> 00:42:58,030
Thanks.

584
00:43:42,559 --> 00:43:45,146
Gruff? Gruff?

585
00:44:00,679 --> 00:44:02,838
Just like the other two.

586
00:44:02,840 --> 00:44:04,949
Just like the drawing.

587
00:44:05,199 --> 00:44:06,581
Over here!

588
00:44:08,239 --> 00:44:10,702
It is head towards summer.

589
00:44:41,400 --> 00:44:43,190
Gruff?

590
00:44:58,920 --> 00:45:00,798
Gruff! There you are.

591
00:45:00,800 --> 00:45:03,181
We have been looking everywhere
for you.

592
00:45:11,079 --> 00:45:14,318
Gruff, it is me, Tinker!
Fawn's friend!

593
00:45:14,320 --> 00:45:17,429
The Scouts are coming for you.
You have to hide!

594
00:45:19,480 --> 00:45:20,559
Gruff?

595
00:45:28,679 --> 00:45:30,141
Tinker!

596
00:45:31,679 --> 00:45:33,391
Tinker?

597
00:45:34,320 --> 00:45:36,239
What did you do?

598
00:45:58,719 --> 00:46:00,465
No.

599
00:46:38,239 --> 00:46:39,621
Help!

600
00:46:40,199 --> 00:46:41,581
Help!

601
00:46:44,079 --> 00:46:45,427
Nyx!

602
00:46:59,599 --> 00:47:01,503
Is she going to be okay?

603
00:47:01,639 --> 00:47:05,262
She needs to rest,
stay off her wings for a few days.

604
00:47:06,360 --> 00:47:07,398
She will be all right.

605
00:47:07,400 --> 00:47:09,438
- Thank goodness.
- That is a relief.

606
00:47:09,440 --> 00:47:12,141
See, Fawn, she is going to be...

607
00:47:12,599 --> 00:47:14,139
Fawn?

608
00:47:29,280 --> 00:47:30,478
Gruff?

609
00:47:31,639 --> 00:47:33,351
Come down.

610
00:47:33,840 --> 00:47:35,903
I need to see you.

611
00:47:48,679 --> 00:47:50,061
Gruff?

612
00:48:09,360 --> 00:48:10,740
Stand firm!

613
00:48:18,119 --> 00:48:19,545
Nightshade powder!

614
00:48:44,440 --> 00:48:46,583
Steady! Hold your ground!

615
00:49:10,199 --> 00:49:12,070
Let us move it out!

616
00:49:28,480 --> 00:49:30,668
You did the right thing.

617
00:50:00,960 --> 00:50:03,838
- Everyone get inside. Hurry!
- This way! Hurry!

618
00:50:03,840 --> 00:50:05,398
Come on, Calista.

619
00:50:09,800 --> 00:50:11,478
Get inside!
Scribble, get inside!

620
00:50:11,480 --> 00:50:12,838
Fly away!
Get out of here!

621
00:50:12,840 --> 00:50:15,666
At least I loved once.

622
00:50:23,679 --> 00:50:26,119
Whatever this is,
it should have stopped by now.

623
00:50:26,119 --> 00:50:27,438
Just stick to the plan.

624
00:50:27,440 --> 00:50:30,278
Immobilize the Never Beast,
and the storm disappears.

625
00:50:33,719 --> 00:50:35,358
Does the storm know the plan?

626
00:50:35,360 --> 00:50:38,344
Get everyone to cover
until this blows over.

627
00:50:50,880 --> 00:50:52,864
Help us!

628
00:51:02,719 --> 00:51:03,998
Get to the shelter!

629
00:51:04,000 --> 00:51:05,159
Move!

630
00:51:05,159 --> 00:51:07,143
And secure the doors!

631
00:51:27,519 --> 00:51:30,983
Stop this! I order you,
stop this now!

632
00:51:48,039 --> 00:51:49,358
Do you need anything else?

633
00:51:49,360 --> 00:51:50,838
Bring some extra bandages.

634
00:51:50,840 --> 00:51:53,039
Tinker. We need to get
to the shelter.

635
00:51:53,039 --> 00:51:54,318
It is not safe here.

636
00:51:54,320 --> 00:51:55,918
I have to find Fawn.

637
00:51:55,920 --> 00:51:57,039
Tinker!

638
00:51:57,039 --> 00:51:58,784
Fawn.

639
00:52:00,360 --> 00:52:03,358
It is over. He cannot hurt
you anymore.

640
00:52:03,360 --> 00:52:04,518
Gruff?

641
00:52:04,519 --> 00:52:07,719
He is exactly what Nyx said
he was a monster.

642
00:52:07,719 --> 00:52:08,958
No, Fawn.

643
00:52:08,960 --> 00:52:10,909
He is my hero.

644
00:52:12,800 --> 00:52:14,181
<i>When I found him in Winter,</i>

645
00:52:14,559 --> 00:52:16,702
<i>he was acting really strange.</i>

646
00:52:18,400 --> 00:52:20,748
Gruff, it is I. Tinker!

647
00:52:20,920 --> 00:52:22,239
Fawn's friend!

648
00:52:22,239 --> 00:52:24,998
The Scouts are coming for you.
You have to hide!

649
00:52:26,679 --> 00:52:27,918
Gruff?

650
00:52:35,679 --> 00:52:40,429
<i>If he had not pushed me away,
The tree. </I> would have crushed me

651
00:52:42,800 --> 00:52:44,278
I could have been killing.

652
00:52:44,280 --> 00:52:45,865
Or worse.

653
00:52:46,159 --> 00:52:48,541
He was protecting you.

654
00:52:48,599 --> 00:52:50,344
He saved my life.

655
00:52:50,840 --> 00:52:52,358
And I betrayed him.

656
00:53:01,320 --> 00:53:02,905
Where are you going?

657
00:53:03,320 --> 00:53:05,588
To do the right thing.

658
00:53:13,599 --> 00:53:16,630
Hang tight, Gruff!
We are getting you out of here!

659
00:53:17,760 --> 00:53:19,639
We need help.

660
00:53:19,639 --> 00:53:21,199
Pull harder!

661
00:53:21,199 --> 00:53:24,981
For goodness' sake,
there is an easier way to do this.

662
00:53:27,119 --> 00:53:28,501
Thank you.

663
00:53:32,280 --> 00:53:33,945
Go! Take cover!

664
00:53:34,239 --> 00:53:36,030
Come on, Gruff!

665
00:53:37,920 --> 00:53:39,358
Gruff, let us go!

666
00:53:40,800 --> 00:53:42,101
Gruff?

667
00:53:45,239 --> 00:53:46,958
- Come on, Fawn!
- Get out of there!

668
00:53:46,960 --> 00:53:48,878
Life or death moment, here!

669
00:53:50,280 --> 00:53:51,318
Listen to me.

670
00:53:51,320 --> 00:53:53,860
You are having a reaction
to the Nightshade.

671
00:54:01,599 --> 00:54:03,344
You can see my glow!

672
00:54:06,880 --> 00:54:07,998
Do not worry, Gruff.

673
00:54:08,000 --> 00:54:09,903
I am going to get you out
of here.

674
00:54:32,000 --> 00:54:34,278
Well, I did not see that coming.

675
00:54:34,280 --> 00:54:35,958
Nyx got it backwards.

676
00:54:35,960 --> 00:54:38,278
He is not here to destroy us.

677
00:54:38,280 --> 00:54:39,719
The towers.

678
00:54:39,719 --> 00:54:42,518
They draw in the lightning,
so he can collect it!

679
00:54:42,519 --> 00:54:45,358
It is what he has been preparing
for the whole time!

680
00:55:03,239 --> 00:55:05,143
I understand.

681
00:55:06,000 --> 00:55:07,599
We are going to the towers.

682
00:55:07,599 --> 00:55:09,039
- No!
- It is too dangerous.

683
00:55:09,039 --> 00:55:11,119
For once, my head and heart,

684
00:55:11,119 --> 00:55:13,559
They are actually telling me
to do the same thing.

685
00:55:13,559 --> 00:55:14,719
Fawn, you cannot!

686
00:55:14,719 --> 00:55:16,351
It is okay.

687
00:55:17,400 --> 00:55:22,278
That said, if things do not go well,
still, you can have my rock collection.

688
00:55:22,280 --> 00:55:23,990
On.

689
00:55:24,920 --> 00:55:26,398
All right, big guy.

690
00:55:26,400 --> 00:55:28,384
Just follow my glow.

691
00:55:37,320 --> 00:55:39,224
Okay, Gruff! That is it!

692
00:55:43,719 --> 00:55:45,021
Pull up!

693
00:55:48,800 --> 00:55:51,501
I am up here!
Higher!

694
00:55:51,519 --> 00:55:53,184
Gruff, fly higher!

695
00:55:55,599 --> 00:55:56,719
Are you okay?

696
00:56:30,280 --> 00:56:31,786
Is that Fawn?

697
00:56:41,000 --> 00:56:42,789
Two down, two to go!

698
00:56:54,519 --> 00:56:56,184
One more, Gruff!

699
00:57:02,119 --> 00:57:03,420
No!

700
00:57:06,679 --> 00:57:07,981
Gruff!

701
00:57:22,159 --> 00:57:23,398
Nyx!

702
00:57:23,400 --> 00:57:24,679
What are you doing?

703
00:57:24,679 --> 00:57:26,599
Saving Pixie Hollow!

704
00:57:26,599 --> 00:57:29,471
No, he was saving Pixie Hollow.

705
00:57:59,239 --> 00:58:01,239
Nyx, we do not have much time.

706
00:58:01,239 --> 00:58:03,065
The fire is spreading fast.

707
00:58:06,360 --> 00:58:07,398
Listen to me.

708
00:58:07,400 --> 00:58:10,782
Get out of here. Get everyone
to safety.

709
00:58:11,480 --> 00:58:12,985
Go!

710
00:58:21,840 --> 00:58:25,302
Gruff, it is too late.
How can we catch it all?

711
00:58:41,119 --> 00:58:42,581
Follow me.

712
01:00:24,800 --> 01:00:25,958
Can you see them?

713
01:00:25,960 --> 01:00:27,260
There!

714
01:00:29,880 --> 01:00:31,226
Fawn!

715
01:00:31,559 --> 01:00:32,907
Help them!

716
01:01:05,280 --> 01:01:06,478
No!
Fawn.

717
01:01:06,480 --> 01:01:07,780
Fawn?

718
01:01:08,079 --> 01:01:10,382
Fawn, wake up!
Is she okay?

719
01:01:14,480 --> 01:01:16,159
No!

720
01:01:16,159 --> 01:01:17,746
This cannot be.

721
01:02:20,000 --> 01:02:21,664
Gruff?

722
01:02:25,159 --> 01:02:28,349
That is my big,
furry monster.

723
01:02:36,679 --> 01:02:37,981
Fawn!

724
01:02:56,199 --> 01:03:00,221
<i>Every fairy should know the true
story about the Never Beast.</i>

725
01:03:02,400 --> 01:03:05,943
<i>He is the brave guardian
of Pixie Hollow.</i>

726
01:03:08,159 --> 01:03:10,701
<i>He is our hero.</i>

727
01:03:11,519 --> 01:03:15,028
<i>And his name is Gruff.</i>

728
01:03:16,039 --> 01:03:18,501
Easy, easy. A little more.

729
01:03:18,519 --> 01:03:20,423
Good job!

730
01:03:32,199 --> 01:03:33,831
<i>Hei? Gruff!</i>

731
01:03:33,880 --> 01:03:35,625
<i>Thanks, Gruff!</i>

732
01:03:36,400 --> 01:03:38,719
Well, how about that?

733
01:03:38,719 --> 01:03:40,278
They finally see
what I see.

734
01:03:46,679 --> 01:03:48,708
Took them long enough.

735
01:03:52,559 --> 01:03:54,668
<i>Hey, Gruff.
Hi, Gruffy.</i>

736
01:03:55,239 --> 01:03:56,918
What do you all think?
We should do now!

737
01:03:56,920 --> 01:03:58,398
Actually, I made a list.

738
01:03:58,400 --> 01:03:59,759
Of course you did.

739
01:03:59,760 --> 01:04:02,188
We should go truffle
snuffling!

740
01:04:02,199 --> 01:04:04,438
<i>With that sense of smell.</i>

741
01:04:04,440 --> 01:04:06,079
<i>Speaking of smells.</i>

742
01:04:06,079 --> 01:04:07,599
How about a bath?

743
01:04:07,599 --> 01:04:11,746
I have a lilac shampoo.
<i>That could do wonder for that fur.</i>

744
01:04:11,760 --> 01:04:14,119
<>I know a hot spring
that is just his size.</i>

745
01:04:14,119 --> 01:04:16,228
<i>With a waterfall!</i>

746
01:04:18,920 --> 01:04:20,585
Fawn?

747
01:04:24,880 --> 01:04:26,181
Gruff?

748
01:04:28,599 --> 01:04:30,119
Looks like he needs a nap.

749
01:04:30,119 --> 01:04:32,148
A little rest will perk him
right up.

750
01:04:32,199 --> 01:04:34,025
<i>Will not it, Fawn?</i>

751
01:04:35,000 --> 01:04:36,664
His work  done.

752
01:04:36,960 --> 01:04:39,739
It is time for him
to go back into hibernation.

753
01:04:40,239 --> 01:04:41,759
About how long are we talking?

754
01:04:41,760 --> 01:04:43,789
A month? A season?

755
01:04:45,480 --> 01:04:47,349
A Year?

756
01:04:50,119 --> 01:04:52,958
More like 1,000 years.

757
01:04:54,239 --> 01:04:55,719
But that means.

758
01:04:55,719 --> 01:04:58,101
We will never see him again.

759
01:05:07,199 --> 01:05:08,864
It is time.

760
01:05:11,280 --> 01:05:16,983
<i>♪ Do you long to be left
all alone.</i>

761
01:05:19,079 --> 01:05:25,148
<i>♪ Set apart with a heart made
of stone.</i>

762
01:05:26,920 --> 01:05:30,349
<i>♪ There is a light
that you shine.</i>

763
01:05:30,440 --> 01:05:32,105
<i>♪ There is a love.</i>

764
01:05:32,599 --> 01:05:36,028
<i>♪ I see it in your eyes.</i>

765
01:05:36,199 --> 01:05:40,391
<i>♪ Every day, every night.</i>

766
01:05:41,840 --> 01:05:45,666
<i>♪ I know time may divide.</i>

767
01:05:45,760 --> 01:05:50,668
<i>♪ But fate is something
we refuse to hide.</i>

768
01:05:51,000 --> 01:05:55,349
<i>♪ And it is real and
it is right.</i>

769
01:05:57,199 --> 01:06:02,710
<i>♪ Something strange
out of sight.</i>

770
01:06:03,519 --> 01:06:08,838
<i>♪ We say good night.</i>

771
01:06:11,039 --> 01:06:13,639
<i>Anyone who sleeps
for 1,000 years.</i>

772
01:06:13,639 --> 01:06:15,862
Deserves a decent bed.

773
01:06:16,280 --> 01:06:18,581
And a fluffy pillow.

774
01:06:20,280 --> 01:06:22,742
Make that a "Gruffy" pillow.

775
01:06:23,320 --> 01:06:26,918
A spring-filled water bowl
that never runs dry.

776
01:06:26,920 --> 01:06:30,588
A night light,
so you never have to be scared.

777
01:06:34,840 --> 01:06:37,871
A little fresh air
to keep you cool.

778
01:06:48,679 --> 01:06:52,826
And the enduring respect
of a grateful Scout.

779
01:07:04,440 --> 01:07:06,389
Hey, big guy.

780
01:07:08,239 --> 01:07:10,065
I will not see you again.

781
01:07:12,559 --> 01:07:15,989
But I know you will always
be there when we need you.

782
